<sect1 id="_DECLARE">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title>#DECLARE</title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para><emphasis role="bold">#<!-- DNT-Start -->DECLARE<!-- DNT-End --><indexterm>
      <primary>#<!-- DNT-Start -->DECLARE<!-- DNT-End --></primary>
    </indexterm>( </emphasis><emphasis>symbol </emphasis><emphasis
  role="bold">);</emphasis></para>

  <para><informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colwidth="76.70pt" />

        <colspec colwidth="276.10pt" />

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>symbol</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

            <entry>The name of the template variable.</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable></para>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold">#<!-- DNT-Start -->DECLARE<!-- DNT-End --> </emphasis>statement declares a
  user-defined <emphasis>symbol</emphasis> for use in the template. The
  <emphasis>symbol</emphasis> is simply created and not initialized to any
  particular value, therefore it may be destined to contain either string or
  numeric data.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting>  #DECLARE(MySymbol); //declare a symbol named "MySymbol"
  #SET(MySymbol,1); //initialize MySymbol to 1
</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="_SET">#<!-- DNT-Start -->SET<!-- DNT-End --></link>, <link linkend="_APPEND">#<!-- DNT-Start -->APPEND<!-- DNT-End --></link></para>
</sect1>
